data.name: [teltonika] TST100
[teltonika] TFT100

children.name: Data Mode
children.description:
0 – Home On Stop
1 – Home On Moving
2 – Roaming On Stop
3 – Roaming On Moving
4 – Unknown On Stop
5 – Unknown On Moving

children.name: Sleep Mode
children.description:
0 - Sleep modes disabled
1 – GNSS sleep
2 – Deep sleep
3 – Online deep sleep
4 - Ultra deep sleep

children.name: GNSS Status
children.description:
0 - GNSS OFF
1 – GNSS ON with fix
2 - GNSS ON without fix
3 - GNSS sleep

children.name: GSM Area Code
children.description: Location Area code (LAC), it depends on GSM operator. It provides unique number which assigned to a set of base GSM stations.

children.name: External Voltage
children.description: IO element is used to measure External Voltage, when External Voltage is < 65V

children.name: ISO6709 Coordinates
children.description:
ISO6709 Coordinates
Latitude, Longitude (in Degrees, Minutes and Seconds) and Altitude:
IO value format: ±DDMMSS.SSSS±DDDMMSS.SSSS±AAA.AAA/

children.name: Geofence zone 01
children.description:
0 – target left zone
1 – target entered zone
2 – over speeding end
3 – over speeding start

children.name: Geofence zone 02
children.description:
0 – target left zone
1 – target entered zone
2 – over speeding end
3 – over speeding start

children.name: Auto Geofence
children.description:
0 – target left zone
1 – target entered zone

children.name: Overspeeding Event
children.description: At over speeding start km/h, at over speeding end km/h

children.name: Last Known Position
children.description: Time in seconds has passed since last GNSS fix

children.name: Master control FW version
children.description: Scooter's PCB and FW versions. First 4 bits (MSB) describe PCB version and the rest 12 bits - FW version. For example, IO value is 0x1101, it means PCB version is 1 and FW version V1.0.1.

children.name: Alarm code
children.description:
9 – alarm for being pushed in lock mode
12 – alarm for high recoil energy during brake

children.name: Lock status
children.description:
0 - Scooter is unlocked
1 - Scooter is locked

children.name: Buzzer alarm status
children.description:
0 - Scooter's buzzer is not active
1 - Scooter's buzzer is active

children.name: External battery status
children.description:
0 - Scooter don't have external battery connected
1 - Scooter has external battery connected

children.name: Actual remaining mileage
children.description: Actual mileage with remaining battery power

children.name: Predicted remaining mileage
children.description: Predicted mileage with remaining battery power

children.name: Supply voltage
children.description: Supply voltage of the central control (system driving voltage)

children.name: Internal battery capacity
children.description: Current residual capacity percentage of internal battery

children.name: External battery capacity
children.description: Current residual capacity percentage of external battery

children.name: Beacon ID's
children.description:
Data structure:

Data part: 1 Byte
Beacon flag: 1 Byte
Beacon ID (iBeacon/Eddystone): 20 Bytes/16 Bytes
Signal strength: 1 Byte

children.name: BT Status
children.description:
0 - BT is disabled
1 - BT Enabled, not device connected
2 - Device connected, BTv3 Only
3 - Device connected, BLE only
4 - Device connected, BLE + BT

children.name: Get version
children.description: Returns code version, device IMEI, modem app version, RTC time, Init time, Uptime and BT MAC address.

children.name: Get GPS
children.description: Current GPS data, date and time.

children.name: Get input/output info
children.description: Readout analog input,digital input and output.

children.name: Get GPS link
children.description: Returns location information with Google maps link.

children.name: Read IO
children.description:
readio #	
Returns IO status, # AVL ID.

children.name: Get FW and restarts
children.description: Get data about FW and restarts

children.name: Get record
children.description: SMS command initiates saving and sending of high priority record

children.name: Get IMEI and CCID
children.description:
Response is sent to SMS/GPRS command sender and also to GSM number provided.

1.# GSM number using international format e.g. 37069012345

children.name: Get IMSI
children.description: Sends the IMSI number of the SIM card inserted as a response to the sender.

children.name: Get state
children.description: Responds with information about hardware and firmware versions and storage space

children.name: Get param #100
children.description:
getparam #

Returns selected parameter value.
1.# - first ID value.
2.# - second ID value.
3.# - third ID value.

children.name: Get params #100 and #179
children.description:
getparam #;#;…

Returns selected parameter value.
1.# - first ID value.
2.# - second ID value.
3.# - third ID value.

children.name: Set param #100
children.description:
setparam #:#

Sets selected parameter value

[Parameter ID] : [New Parameter Value] ; [Parameter ID] : [New Parameter Value]...

children.name: Set params #100 and #179
children.description:
setparam #:#;#:#;…

Sets selected parameter value

[Parameter ID] : [New Parameter Value] ; [Parameter ID] : [New Parameter Value]...

children.name: Redirects to other server
children.description:
flush #,#,#,#,#,#,#

Redirects device to other server.
1.# - IMEI.
2.# - APN.
3.# - LOGIN.
4.# - PASS.
5.# - IP.
6.# - PORT.
7.# - MODE (0-TCP/1-UDP).

children.name: Delete records
children.description: Delete all records from SD card.

children.name: Set key
children.description:
setkey # #

Add new or change current configuration keyword. If device is locked, keyword cannot be changed.
1.# - old keyword (if adding new keyword space).
2.# - new keyword.

children.name: Delete key
children.description:
delkey #

Remove existing keyword (If device is locked, keyword cannot be changed).
1.# - old keyword.

children.name: Get black box
children.description:
bbread #

Return black box information (HEX value of event ID and HEX value of custom data field (optional)).
1.# - returns entered number of latest events. When # is omitted the latest events are packed to single SMS.

children.name: Get black box HEX
children.description:
bbinfo #

Return same information as bbread command but additional all events timestamp is written in HEX.
1.# - returns entered number of latest events. When # is omitted the latest events are packed to single SMS.

children.name: Get Bluetooth list
children.description:
Returns requested Bluetooth list.
# - 0,1 or 2 (0 – Discovered, 1 – Paired, 2 – Connected, 3 – Discovered BT4/BLE devices).

children.name: Set visible 10 sec
children.description:
Sets Bluetooth to visible with TMO.
# - visibility TMO (from 1 to 255 seconds).

children.name: Disconnect
children.description:
Disconnects from current device and pauses auto connect functionality for TMO.
# - none or TMO (from 1 to 255 seconds).

children.name: Unpair
children.description:
Unpair Bluetooth device.
# - all, BT address (all – unpair all devices, BT address – unpair only specified MAC address).

children.name: Set odometer
children.description:
Set total odometer value.

odoset:#
# - new odometer value in km.

children.name: Stop tracking
children.description:
Note: This command is supported from 55.00.00 firmware version.

on_demand_tracking#

Tracking on Demand functionality. # = Value ↓
0 – Stops Tracking on Demand functionality.
1 – Starts Tracking on Demand functionality.
2 – Generates one high priority record and inititates data sending to server.

children.name: Start tracking
children.description:
Note: This command is supported from 55.00.00 firmware version.

on_demand_tracking#

Tracking on Demand functionality. # = Value ↓
0 – Stops Tracking on Demand functionality.
1 – Starts Tracking on Demand functionality.
2 – Generates one high priority record and inititates data sending to server.

children.name: Unlock
children.description:
Used to lock/unlock E-Scooter. 

sclockctrl #
# = Value ↓
0 - Unlock
1 - Lock

children.name: Lock
children.description:
Used to lock/unlock E-Scooter. 

sclockctrl #
# = Value ↓
0 - Unlock
1 - Lock

children.name: Set kilometers
children.description:
Used to change units. 

scsetunits #
# = Value ↓
0 - Kilometers (km)
1 - Miles (mi)

children.name: Reset single time
children.description:
Resets internal E-Scooter counters. 

scrstcnt #
# = Value ↓
1 - single time
2 - total mileage
3 - total

children.name: Reset total mileage
children.description:
Resets internal E-Scooter counters. 

scrstcnt #
# = Value ↓
1 - single time
2 - total mileage
3 - total

children.name: Reset total
children.description:
Resets internal E-Scooter counters. 

scrstcnt #
# = Value ↓
1 - single time
2 - total mileage
3 - total

children.name: Allow headlight control
children.description:
This option disallows headlight control by scledctrl command, if LED switch is set to 1 (scledswitch 1) 

scsetledswitch #
# = Value ↓
0 - disable
1 - enable

children.name: Disallow headlight control
children.description:
This option disallows headlight control by scledctrl command, if LED switch is set to 1 (scledswitch 1) 

scsetledswitch #
# = Value ↓
0 - disable
1 - enable

children.name: Turn OFF LED
children.description:
Turns ON/OFF LED but only if -> scsetledswitch 0, 

scledctrl
# = Value ↓
0 - Turn OFF
1 - Turn ON

children.name: Turn ON LED
children.description:
Turns ON/OFF LED but only if -> scsetledswitch 0, 

scledctrl
# = Value ↓
0 - Turn OFF
1 - Turn ON

children.name: Set BT pairing code
children.description:
Sets BT pairing code.

scsetbtcode ######
###### - 6 digits BT pairing code

children.name: Set E-Scooter's Speed limit
children.description:
Sets E-Scooter's Speed limit.

scsetspdlim <arg1> <arg2>
<arg1> - Mode
<arg2> - Speed limit

children.name: Set E-Scooter's operating mode
children.description:
Sets E-Scooter's operating mode. 

scsetmode #
# = Value ↓
0 - NORMAL
1 - ECO
2 - SPORT

children.name: Start or shut down the engine
children.description:
Start or shut down the engine. 

scenginectrl #
# = Value ↓
0 - Turn OFF the engine
1 - Turn ON the engine

children.name: Restart
children.description: Restart E-Scooter's system. Restart is available only in non-riding mode. Corresponding mark will be reset after completion of the operation.

children.name: Cruise control switch
children.description:
Cruise control switch. 

scsetcruiseswitch #
# = Value ↓
0 - OFF
1 - ON

children.name: Enable looking for
children.description:
Enable looking for scooter functionality. Initiates headlight and taillight flash + buzzer beep. 

sclookfor #
# = Value ↓
0 - OFF
1 - ON

children.name: Beep control switch
children.description:
Beep control switch. 

scsetbeepswitch #
# = Value ↓
0 - OFF
1 - ON

children.name: Buzzer control
children.description:
IoT buzzer control.

scbuzzerctrl <arg1> <arg2>
<arg1> - 0 - OFF; 1 - ON
<arg2> - timeout (sec)

children.name: Get speed limit
children.description:
Returns Speed limit value for chosen operating mode. 

scgetspdlim #
# = Value
0 - NORMAL mode
1 - ECO mode
2 - SPORT mode

children.name: Beep control on alarm
children.description:
Beep control on alarm.

scsetalarmswitch <arg>
<arg> - 0 - OFF; 1 - ON

children.name: Functions setup
children.description:
E-Scooter's functions setup.

scsetconfig <arg1> <arg2>
<arg1> - 0 - 1st instruction set; 1 - 2nd instruction set
<arg2> - 2 bytes value where each bit controls separate parameter

children.name: Firmware update
children.description:
E-Scooter's firmware update force command.

sciap <arg>
<arg> - 0 – Master control, 1 – BMS1 (internal battery), 2 - BMS2 (external battery), 3 - Instrument panel (scooter head), 4 – Cable Lock (Wired)

children.name: Open battery lock
children.description: Opens battery lock for battery replacement

data.description:
Teltonika TST100
Professional waterproof tracker designed for E-scooters with internal high gain GNSS/GSM antennas and internal Li-ion battery. 

Manual https://wiki.teltonika-mobility.com/view/TST100_Manual
 
Commands description https://wiki.teltonika-sas.com/view/TST100_SMS/GPRS_Commands
